# Welcome to our first blog post!

This is an example blog post written in MDX. You can use both Markdown and JSX components here.

## Why Cats are Not Doctors

Despite their many talents, cats have not yet mastered medical science. Here's why:

1. They lack opposable thumbs
2. They sleep 16 hours a day
3. They're more interested in chasing laser pointers than studying anatomy

But that doesn't mean they can't make you feel better!

# Markdown Examples

This post demonstrates various markdown and MDX features.

## Text Formatting

**Bold text** and *italic text* are supported.

## Lists

Unordered list:
- Item 1
- Item 2
  - Nested item
  - Another nested item
- Item 3

Ordered list:
1. First item
2. Second item
3. Third item

## Code Blocks

```javascript
function hello() {
  console.log("Hello, world!");
}
```

Inline `code` is also supported.

## Blockquotes

> This is a blockquote.
> It can span multiple lines.

## Custom Components

<Note>
  This is a custom note component!
</Note>

<Note type="warning">
  This is a warning message.
</Note>

<Note type="error">
  This is an error message.
</Note>
